  "prompt": "Why did Pepper Potts leave Tony Stark in Captain America: Civil War? Why wasn\u2019t she in the film?",
  "response": "In *Captain America: Civil War*, Pepper Potts is notably absent, and her absence is explained by the events surrounding Tony Stark's character. At that point in the Marvel Cinematic Universe (MCU), Tony and Pepper are dealing with the aftermath of the conflicts resulting from the Avengers\u2019 activities, particularly those that led to significant destruction and loss of life.\n\nDuring the film, it is implied that Pepper and Tony have taken a step back from their relationship due to the pressure and strain caused by the superhero lifestyle, particularly after the events of *Avengers: Age of Ultron*. Although the film doesn't provide a detailed explanation of their relationship status, it suggests that they have separated or are on rocky terms because of the stresses related to the Sokovia Accords and Tony's involvement in the superhero registration debate.\n\nGwyneth Paltrow, who plays Pepper Potts, was not part of the film due to scheduling conflicts, which also contributed to her absence from the story. The filmmakers chose not to include Pepper to maintain the focus on the character dynamics and the broader conflict among the Avengers.",
